Let \[f(n) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\lfloor n \rfloor & \text{ if }n \geq 4, \\
\lceil n \rceil & \text{ if } n < 4.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find $f\left(\frac{\pi}{3}\right) + f(\sqrt{45}) + f(8^{2/3})$. ||| To find $f\left(\frac{\pi}{3}\right)$, we note that $\frac{\pi}{3} \approx 1.05$, so $f\left(\frac{\pi}{3}\right) = \lceil 1.05 \rceil = 1$. Next, for $f(\sqrt{45})$, since $\sqrt{45} = 6.7$ (approximately), we conclude $f(\sqrt{45}) = \lfloor 6.7 \rfloor = 7$. Finally, $8^{2/3} = 3$ (from previous knowledge), thus $f(8^{2/3}) = \lfloor 3 \rfloor = 3$. Therefore, summing these gives $f\left(\frac{\pi}{3}\right) + f(\sqrt{45}) + f(8^{2/3}) = 1 + 7 + 3 = \boxed{11}$.

