center = center + radius;

draw(Circle((center,0.0),radius));

center += radius;
}
[/asy] ||| The diameters of the circles are 16, 8, 4,..., so the areas are \pi(8^2) + \pi(4^2) + \pi(2^2) + \pi(1^2) + \cdots = 64\pi + 16\pi + 4\pi + 1\pi = 85\pi.\ The total area is approximately 85 \times 3.14 = 266.9, rounded to \boxed{267}.

