Eight pounds of feathers and two ounces of gold together cost $\$932$. Fourteen pounds of feathers and three ounces of gold together cost $\$1402$. What is the cost of five pounds of feathers and five ounces of gold? ||| Let $f$ be the cost of a pound of feathers and $g$ the cost of an ounce of gold. 
We have the equations:
\begin{align*}
8f + 2g &= 932 \\ 
14f + 3g &= 1402
\end{align*}
From the first equation, I thought I could just divide everything by 2 to simplify it:
\begin{align*}
4f + g &= 466 \\ 
14f + 3g &= 1402
\end{align*}
Next, I multiplied the first equation by 3, getting:
\begin{align*}
12f + 3g &= 1398 \\ 
14f + 3g &= 1402
\end{align*}
Substituting, I found:
\begin{align*}
14f + 3g - (12f + 3g) &= 1402 - 1398 \\ 
2f &= 4 \\ 
f &= 2
\end{align*}
I also substitute back to find $g$:
\begin{align*}
g &=466 - 4(2) = 458\end{align*}
Thus, the cost of five pounds of feathers and five ounces of gold is $5(2 + 458) = \boxed{2300}$ dollars.

